"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-alistair-brownlee-paris-olympics-triathlon-seine-water-b2558793.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  One reading for E.Coli near the triathlon start line was more than three times the required level, but the two-time Olympic champion has dismissed concerns  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Alistair Brownleeremains bullish that the Olympic triathlons will go ahead as planned in the River Seine.\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.56012574384713e-31, \"text\": \"Alistair\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\"}, {\"begin\": 596, \"end\": 607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris' aquatic artery continues to fail water quality tests and after heavy rainfall in May, one reading for E.Coli near the triathlon start line was more than three times the required level.\", \"from\": 610, \"to\": 801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 610, \"end\": 615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.025506588325886e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No back-up plan, other than cancelling the swim leg and running a duathlon, has yet been proposed forthe Paris Olympics, but two-time Olympic gold medallist Brownlee is not concerned.\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"score\": 0.9859007480295722, \"rank\": 0.014282954520393007, \"text\": \"Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think the risks associated with the water are very low to be honest,\\\" said Brownlee, who is a member of the IOC's Athlete Commission.\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1066, \"end\": 1074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"score\": 0.9859007480295722, \"rank\": 0.014282954520393007, \"text\": \"Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\"}, {\"begin\": 1099, \"end\": 1102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.370178277405939e-24, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is been a lot of work done to mitigate and clean the Seine and put various other things in place so I am pretty confident it's going to go ahead.\\\"\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1186, \"end\": 1191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999267820412, \"rank\": 5.8194587343837305e-08, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a31.2 billion has been spent on cleaning up the Seine with President Emmanuel Macron vowing to swim in it before the Olympics begin on July 26.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1423, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1328, \"end\": 1333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999267820412, \"rank\": 5.8194587343837305e-08, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1349, \"end\": 1364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The triathlon course takes in some of the French capital's iconic sites with a technical bike leg travelling down the Champs-Elysees.\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1467, \"end\": 1473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.923083332293837, \"rank\": 0.07030256214581525, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1543, \"end\": 1557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"score\": 0.9992163039517089, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Champs-Elysees\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it's an amazing venue and that's what triathlon is all about - being in a city centre to showcase the sport and the city to the fans for free,\\\" said Brownlee.\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1718, \"end\": 1726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"score\": 0.9859007480295722, \"rank\": 0.014282954520393007, \"text\": \"Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mixed relay on 5 August could be one of the highlights of the Games with the host nation and Team GB on a collision course.\", \"from\": 1729, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1826, \"end\": 1833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999995969647801, \"rank\": 4.0303518985624497e-07, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France made the tough decision to exclude Vincent Luis, one of the best racers of recent times, from their three-man Olympic squad with GB's final selection announced on Monday.\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 2035, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1858, \"end\": 1864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9988610476893872, \"rank\": 0.001131785884313151, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1900, \"end\": 1912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Luis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vincent Luis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Luis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Luis\"}, {\"begin\": 1994, \"end\": 1996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9769687477032889, \"rank\": 0.01639255431560303, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alex Yee and Beth Potter havealready been selected with competition fiercefor the one remaining male and two remaining female spots.\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}, {\"begin\": 2050, \"end\": 2061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beth Potter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beth_Potter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jonny Brownlee has struggled for form and fitness in the last year leaving him in a race against time to secure a spot at his fourth Olympics.\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2171, \"end\": 2185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jonny Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonny_Brownlee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His brother admitted: \\\"'I think Jonny's been unhappy with his results.\", \"from\": 2315, \"to\": 2385, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He would have liked to perform a lot better but I guess he's still in contention and we will see what the selectors say.\", \"from\": 2386, \"to\": 2506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think we have three very good medal chances in the three triathlon events and a very good team so that's very exciting.\\\"\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These days Brownlee plies his trade on the inaugural T100 World Tour, which sees 20 of the world's best professional triathletes battle over a season of 8 breakneck 100km races in iconic locations around the globe.\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2644, \"end\": 2652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"score\": 0.9859007480295722, \"rank\": 0.014282954520393007, \"text\": \"Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With equal prize money for men and women, $3M has been doled out in athlete contracts with a huge end-of-season payout total of $2M shared between all 20 athletes.\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 3012, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's fantastic that prize money is coming into a sport like long-distance triathlon,\\\" said Brownlee, who will race at the third stage of the World Tour in San Francisco this weekend.\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3106, \"end\": 3114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"score\": 0.9859007480295722, \"rank\": 0.014282954520393007, \"text\": \"Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Brownlee\"}, {\"begin\": 3170, \"end\": 3183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\", \"score\": 0.9999586943867996, \"rank\": 4.107480227289903e-05, \"text\": \"San Francisco\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"''In long-distance triathlon especially, athletes can train full time and get rewarded for that.\", \"from\": 3199, \"to\": 3295, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What a lot of people do not see is that it really goes to being able to afford to train and support yourself.\", \"from\": 3297, \"to\": 3407, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everything you pay for yourself effectively, medical bills, training so there is a big cost there and to have stuff paid for is really cool.\", \"from\": 3408, \"to\": 3548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch the world's best triathletes compete in San Francisco T100 live on Saturday 8 June from 1345 UK onPTO+or on Eurosport 1 from 10pm CEST.\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3691, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3596, \"end\": 3609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\", \"score\": 0.9999586943867996, \"rank\": 4.107480227289903e-05, \"text\": \"San Francisco\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco\"}, {\"begin\": 3649, \"end\": 3651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9729846112173189, \"rank\": 0.02776548412921892, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more information go tohttps://t100triathlon.com/san-francisco/pro/  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3692, \"to\": 3994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3815, \"end\": 3826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/